The paper discusses the advances in robotic technology and research in human-robot collaboration, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). It also reviews neuroscientific and psychological findings related to human-human interaction, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the need for active decision making in robots, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the mechanisms required for physical collaboration, which involves neural networks (cs.NE).
